land\\\">England<\\/a>. A company limited by guarantee may be with or without having&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Share capital\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Share_capital\\\">share capital<\\/a>.<\\/li>\\n<li style=\\\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\\\"><b>A&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"Private company limited by shares\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Private_company_limited_by_shares\\\">company limited by shares<\\/a>:<\\/b>&nbsp;The most common form of the company used for business ventures. Specifically, a limited company is a \\\"company in which the liability of each shareholder is limited to the amount individually invested\\\" with corporations being \\\"the most common example of a limited company\\\".<sup id=\\\"cite_ref-Black\'s_9-1\\\" class=\\\"reference\\\" style=\\\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\\\"><a style=\\\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Company#cite_note-Black\'s-9\\\">[9]<\\/a><\\/sup>&nbsp;This type of company is common in&nbsp;<a style=\\\"color: #0b0080; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\" title=\\\"England\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/En